          { type: 'text', content: '<p>The 2025 correction was bowling-driven. Middle-overs economy improved by 1.69 runs per over, the single biggest year-on-year improvement in any phase across all ten teams. Bumrah\'s 6.17 middle-overs economy (30 overs, MEDIUM) and Santner\'s 7.18 (45 overs, HIGH) created the platform. Death bowling improved by nearly a run per over. The batting peaked in the powerplay (155.7, up 12.1 from 2024) and death (179.3, elite). The middle overs dipped slightly, but the bowling improvement more than compensated.</p>' },
          { type: 'text', content: '<p><strong>Squad-Building Philosophy:</strong> MI build from the top down. The big four (Bumrah, SKY, Pandya, Rohit) consume 67.00 Cr, 55.6% of the total salary on four players. This is a franchise that believes in star concentration: pay market rate for the best players in the world, fill around them with value signings, and trust that individual brilliance will overcome structural gaps. It has worked five times. The question is whether it works in 2026 with a squad that has the league\'s best bowling attack and an opener combination that has yet to push the powerplay batting from merely above-average to genuinely commanding.</p>' }
