          { type: 'text', content: '<p>The phase distribution confirms the structural issue: Khaleel\'s death economy of 11.58 (31 overs, HIGH sample) is 0.7 runs above the league average. He takes wickets (18) but concedes too many runs doing it. The death bowling relies heavily on Noor Ahmad, whose 8.41 economy in 21.2 death overs (MEDIUM) is genuinely exceptional for a wrist spinner. But asking a 20-year-old to carry both the middle overs (77.1% of his overs) and the death (16.0% of his overs) is a workload equation with no margin for injury.</p>' },
          { type: 'text', content: '<p>> <strong>Data Coverage Note:</strong> All statistics are drawn from Cricsheet\'s ball-by-ball T20 archive (9,496 matches through January 31, 2026). Major tournaments covered: IPL (2008-2025), BBL (2011-2026), ILT20 (2023-2026), SMAT (2016-2024/25, partial), CPL, PSL, The Hundred, SA20, Super Smash, and bilateral T20I series. Cross-tournament intelligence uses a weighted composite model; see stat pack for methodology.</p>' }
