          { type: 'text', content: '<p>Everything clicked offensively. Powerplay SR surged to 159.1, middle overs hit 147.6, and the death batting exploded to 190.1. But the bowling tells a different story: economy worsened in the powerplay (9.41, up from 9.05) and the middle overs (9.34, up from 8.60). The death bowling stayed flat at 11.38. Punjab won through outscoring opponents, not through bowling discipline. That is both the identity and the fragility.</p>' },
          { type: 'text', content: '<p><strong>Squad-Building Philosophy:</strong> Punjab have built an all-rounder-heavy squad (9 of 22 players) that prioritizes batting depth over bowling specialization. With Stoinis, Shashank Singh, Omarzai, Jansen, and Harpreet Brar all offering dual utility, the XII can bat to #8 comfortably. The philosophy is unmistakable: outscore the opposition. The 2025 evidence suggests it works. The question is whether it works for two consecutive years.</p>' }
