          { type: 'text', content: '<p>The most significant matchup story is the RCB collapse: from a historically even 18-19 all-time record to 1-6 since 2023. Punjab have been unable to crack RCB\'s bowling attack in the current cycle. The SRH record (0-4 since 2023) is equally concerning and longer-standing; Punjab have never figured out how to beat SRH\'s pace-heavy approach.</p>' },
          { type: 'text', content: '<p>The CSK reversal is the positive counterpoint: from a 15-16 all-time deficit to 4-1 since 2023. Chahal\'s 7.71 economy against CSK (84 balls, MEDIUM) and the batting lineup\'s comfort against CSK\'s spin-heavy middle overs are the drivers. If Punjab can replicate this level of performance against two or three more opponents, the overall win rate lifts meaningfully.</p>' }
